WorldStage Newsonline– The Enugu Electricity Distribution Company PLC (EEDC) has blamed system collapse for power outages in Abia, Anambra, Ebonyi, Enugu, Imo states. In a notice to its customer,  EEDC  informed them of a system collapse which occurred at 6.49pm on Sunday, 12th June, 2022, saying, as a result of the development, all its outgoing feeders were out and this affected supply to customers in the South East states. “We are on standby, awaiting further information on restoration of supply from the National Control Centre (NCC),” the notice said.